      "content": "{\"claim\": \"No unimodal critic score suffices; harness strictly beats self-consistency only when critic confidence is bimodal with a high-confidence error mode and a low-confidence correct mode, making the score distribution a mixture where the error mode captures wrong-majority sets.\",\"mechanism\": \"The repository's data show that a critic with a unimodal score distribution centered at 0.5 yields no filtering benefit because veto and allow regions have equal error rates. The causal failure is the lack of score distribution bimodality. If instead the critic's score distribution is a mixture of two Gaussians, one centered high (error mode) and one centered low (correct mode), then thresholding at the valley between modes separates wrong-majority from right-majority sets. The strict advantage regime is characterized by the separation between mixture components: for any base error rate, there exists a threshold at the distribution valley that yields positive net benefit if and only if the Bhattacharyya distance between the error-mode and correct-mode score distributions exceeds a critical value.\",\"scope\": {\"covers\": [\"bimodal critic score distribution\", \"mixture model separation threshold\", \"base error 0.40-0.70\", \"any k >= 5\"],\"excludes\": [\"unimodal critic score distribution\", \"Bhattacharyya distance between modes is zero\"]},\"forbidden\": [{\"case\": \"Critic score distribution is unimodal (Hartigan dip test p > 0.05) yet thresholded harness strictly beats SC on >= 50% of questions\",\"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"},{\"case\": \"Score distribution is bimodal (Hartigan dip test p < 0.05) but thresholding at the valley does not yield positive net-fixed-minus-broke averaged over the test set\",\"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"}],\"prose_notes\": \"Experiment: 104 questions; k=5; fit Gaussian mixture to critic scores; test for bimodality via Hartigan dip test; threshold at mixture valley. Confirm: (1) bimodality is present; (2) valley threshold yields strict improvement over SC; (3) unimodal critic does not.\"}",
      "changed_fields": ["claim", "mechanism", "scope.covers", "scope.excludes", "forbidden", "prose_notes"]
