      "content": "{\"claim\": \"No static critic suffices; harness strictly beats self-consistency only when critic confidence is dynamically updated via Bayesian belief revision across candidate generation rounds, making the veto decision condition on accumulated evidence rather than a single snapshot.\",\"mechanism\": \"The repository's data show that a critic evaluating only the final candidate set yields zero net benefit because it cannot distinguish convergence due to correctness from convergence due to systematic bias. The causal failure is the critic's lack of temporal context. If instead the critic maintains a Bayesian posterior over majority correctness, updating after each candidate generation round, and the harness vetoes when the posterior probability of error exceeds threshold tau, then the critic can detect systematic bias (posterior remains high across rounds) versus stochastic variation (posterior decreases with more candidates). The strict advantage regime is characterized by the posterior's temporal trajectory: for any base error rate, there exists a posterior threshold tau and a number of rounds n such that the expected net-fixed-minus-broke is positive if and only if the posterior trajectory slope for wrong-majority sets is significantly less negative than for right-majority sets.\",\"scope\": {\"covers\": [\"Bayesian belief revision across candidate rounds\", \"posterior-thresholded veto policy\", \"base error 0.40-0.70\", \"any k >= 5 with sequential candidate generation\"]},\"excludes\": [\"static critic evaluating only final candidate set\", \"posterior trajectories for right and wrong majorities have identical slopes\"]},\"forbidden\": [{\"case\": \"Posterior trajectory slopes for right-majority and wrong-majority sets are indistinguishable (t-test p > 0.05) yet dynamic Bayesian harness strictly beats SC on >= 50% of questions\",\"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"},{\"case\": \"Posterior trajectory slopes differ significantly (t-test p < 0.05) but no posterior threshold tau yields positive net-fixed-minus-broke averaged over the test set\",\"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"}],\"prose_notes\": \"Experiment: 104 questions; generate k=5 candidates sequentially; critic updates Bayesian prior after each candidate; sweep posterior threshold tau; compare with static critic. Confirm: (1) posterior slopes differ; (2) dynamic harness beats SC; (3) static does not.\"}",
